title: Two People Shot By Federal Border Patrol Agent In Portland, Oregon | 10 News
description: Two people are in hospital after a shooting involving federal agents in Portland on Thursday just a day after an ICE officer shot and killed 37-year-old mother of three, Renee Good, in Minnesota.  The Department of Homeland Security said the shooting happened while Border Patrol agents were conducting a "targeted" stop on a vehicle in Oregon carrying two people allegedly affiliated with the Tren de Aragua gang.  "When agents identified themselves to the vehicle occupants, the driver weaponised his vehicle and attempted to run over the law enforcement agents," DHS said in a statement.  The agent fired “defensive shots” before the driver drove off with the passenger and fled the scene. title: Vice President JD Vance Blames Victim Of Fatal ICE Shooting In Minneapolis | 10 News
description: Vice President JD Vance has cast blame as he responded to reporters' questioning about an ICE officer's fatal shooting of 37-year-old mother of three, Renee Good, in Minneapolis.  Speaking to reporters during a White House briefing Vance said, “I can believe that her death is a tragedy while also recognising that it's a tragedy of her own making and a tragedy of the far left who has marshaled an entire movement, a lunatic fringe against our law enforcement officers.”  He defended the federal immigration agent responsible for Wednesday’s fatal shooting and stated he was doing his job as a federal officer and is protected by “absolute immunity”.  Vance also warned European leaders should take President Trump "seriously" on his push to bring Greenland under US control. title: Queensland Farmer's Cattle Lost To Mass Floods | 10 News+
description: Queensland’s north-west has been devastated by floods after weeks of torrential rain. Farmers are bracing for huge losses, with around 30,000 head of livestock estimated to be dead or missing.  Local grazier Beau Harrington from Julia Creek’s Brinard Station spoke to 10 News+ about the harrowing experience of dealing with the destruction. title: Three Missing In Victoria As Firefighters Battle 40 Bushfires Across State | 10 News+
description: Catastrophic bushfires are wreaking havoc across Victoria’s north, east and west as 700 firefighters battle to contain them.   Dozens of towns are under emergency warnings and evacuation orders, with conditions described as being similar to the Black Summer bushfires of 2019-20.   The Longwood fire has consumed a community centre and multiple homes in the township of Ruffy, and three people are missing in Longwood East - last seen standing outside their home as the flames approached. title: What Will The Royal Commission Into Antisemitism In Australia Achieve? | 10 News+
description: Prime Minister Anthony Albanese has performed a political backflip, announcing a Royal Commission into the Bondi Beach attack after weeks of pressure.   So what is a Royal Commission, and what will this one achieve? A Royal Commission is Australia’s highest form of public inquiry, and there have been 140 since Federation, looking at subjects such as police corruption, institutional child abuse, and financial mismanagement.   This specific one will examine four key areas: the prevalence of antisemitism, how law enforcement will respond to antisemitism, the circumstances surrounding the Bondi attack, and how to strengthen social cohesion. title: Catastrophic Victoria Bushfires, Royal Commission Explained, Politicians Spending Scandal | 10 News+
description: Catastrophic bushfires are wreaking havoc across Victoria’s north, east and west as 700 firefighters battle to contain them. Dozens of towns are under emergency warnings and evacuation orders, with conditions described as being similar to the Black Summer bushfires of 2019-20. The Longwood fire has consumed a community centre and multiple homes in the township of Ruffy, and three people are missing in Longwood East - last seen standing outside their home as the flames approached.  Prime Minister Anthony Albanese has performed a political backflip, announcing a Royal Commission into the Bondi Beach attack after weeks of pressure. So what is a Royal Commission, and what will this one achieve? A Royal Commission is Australia’s highest form of public inquiry, and there have been 140 since Federation, looking at subjects such as police corruption, institutional child abuse, and financial mismanagement. This specific one will examine four key areas: the prevalence of antisemitism, how law enforcement will respond to antisemitism, the circumstances surrounding the Bondi attack, and how to strengthen social cohesion.  Federal politicians have been accused of paying off their own mortgages with taxpayer dollars. Under the current rules, it is legal for MPs to use their travel allowance even when staying in homes in Canberra owned by themselves or their spouses. Unlike other Australian cities which have two rates for travel allowances, Canberra has a single flat rate, allowing politicians to claim the same amount even if they aren’t spending money on a hotel room.
